Title : 2014 British Rally Championship
Text : {{Motorsport season
|series = British Rally Championship
|year = 2014
|next = 2016
}}

The '''2014 MSA British Rally Championship''' was the 56th season of the [[British Rally Championship]]. The season began on 3 May in [[Carlisle, Cumbria|Carlisle]] with the [[Pirelli Richard Burns Foundation Rally]] and ended on 13 September in [[Douglas, Isle of Man|Douglas]] with the [[Rally Isle of Man|Rally Isle of Man powered by Microgaming]].

The championship was won by the Irish crew of Daniel McKenna and Arthur Kierans,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rallybrc.co.uk/latest-news/1734-mckenna-and-kierans-are-2014-brc-champions-full-story.html|title=McKenna and Kierans are 2014 BRC champions|work=[[British Rally Championship]]|publisher=UK Rally Limited|date=13 September 2014|accessdate=13 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140914002258/http://www.rallybrc.co.uk/latest-news/1734-mckenna-and-kierans-are-2014-brc-champions-full-story.html|archive-date=14 September 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> who won four of the season's six rallies, to win the championship by eleven points ahead of Osian Pryce and Dale Furniss; Pryce and Furniss won the other two events to be held.

==Event calendar and results==

The 2014 calendar consisted of six rounds at five events with a double header held at the [[Rally Isle of Man]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rallybrc.co.uk/events.html|title=2014 Calendar|work=rallybrc.co.uk|publisher=UK Rally Limited|accessdate=24 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411212932/http://www.rallybrc.co.uk/events.html|archive-date=11 April 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref> A seventh event, [[Rallye Dorset]], was cancelled in July.<ref name="Dorset">{{cite news|url=http://www.rallybrc.co.uk/latest-news/1714-2014-rallye-dorset-postponed-statement-by-the-southern-car-club.html|title=2014 Rallye Dorset postponed, statement by the Southern Car Club|work=[[British Rally Championship]]|publisher=UK Rally Limited|date=12 July 2014|accessdate=12 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714171934/http://www.rallybrc.co.uk/latest-news/1714-2014-rallye-dorset-postponed-statement-by-the-southern-car-club.html|archive-date=14 July 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

