==Championship standings==

===Drivers' championship===
A driver's best five scores counted towards the final championship standings.<ref name="Dorset"/> Points were awarded to the highest placed registered driver on each event as follows: 20, 18, 16, 15, and so on deleting one point per placing down to one single point for all finishers. The second leg of the Rally Isle of Man awarded points at a coefficient of 1.5; thus 30 points were awarded to its winner.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rallybrc.co.uk/latest-news/1725-brc-s-isle-of-man-finale.html|title=BRC's Isle of Man finale|work=[[British Rally Championship]]|publisher=UK Rally Limited|date=8 September 2014|accessdate=13 September 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140914002301/http://www.rallybrc.co.uk/latest-news/1725-brc-s-isle-of-man-finale.html|archive-date=14 September 2014|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

